One person was killed while two others were injured when a taxi and a light motor vehicle collided on Vanguard Drive in Athlone early on Wednesday. In confirming this, ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said a secondary collision occurred when a taxi ran into the rear of a law-enforcement vehicle servicing the scene. Fortunately no one had been injured in the second collision, he added. Meiring said ER24 paramedics had arrived at approximately 9.20 am on the scene of the first accident, where they found Metro and Life Healthcare already in attendance. . 
 
“Upon closer inspection, paramedics found a taxi lying on its side in the right-hand lane while the light motor vehicle was in the middle of the road.
 
“When paramedics assessed the patients, they found the passenger of the light motor vehicle had sustained numerous injuries and showed no signs of life. Unfortunately, nothing could be done and the patient was declared dead on the scene.
 
“The driver of the taxi, along with one other person, were assessed and found to have sustained moderate injuries. Both patients were treated for their injuries and were thereafter transported to a nearby hospital by the Metro Services,” said Meiring..
 
He added that local authorities were on the scene for further investigations. 